HEADWORD: cacao
<hw>ca*ca"o</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., fr. Mex.
<ets>kakahuatl</ets>. Cf. <er>Cocoa</er>, <er>Chocolate</er>]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small evergreen tree (<spn>Theobroma
Cacao</spn>) of South America and the West Indies. Its fruit contains an
edible pulp, inclosing seeds about the size of an almond, from which
cocoa, chocolate, and broma are prepared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

